<b>A few comments - </b>3/27/01 3:31:21 PM<br>~ <b>Balalyka</b><blockquote>A comment on &quot;line of sight&quot;:  Once when I was mainly chattering to my guild, I put this song on and left it on, just for snicks.  I was at the West Gate in FP.  It continued to TP me around for a while, till I was back past Boomba the Big.  Then suddenly, I was outside the gate, in the newbie area.  I let the song go for a while more, but I did not TP through (over?) the wall again.<br><br>As far as general comments, the song has limited usefulness.  You need to TELL your group you plan to use it (though the few times I told my group and then used it, they got mad and said they didn't know what was going on).  It is best in open areas, as it could mean your group's death if you are anywhere near pits of mobs (e.g. basement of Unrest-type places).  Also, you have to make sure to turn it off after you TP, or else you will continue to hear that sucking sound every 3 seconds.  <br><br>Once when I fell in the lava pit under the stairs in Sol A, a fellow Bard suggested that, if I fell in again, I should try this song (I avoided falling back in, so I did not test its usefulness).  Just a thought, as far as getting out of tough places.<br><br>It is a good song for the arena, if you do PVP, since it confuses your opponent.  <br><br>Balalyka<br>Bard of the 31st Season</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
